Sebastian Vettel led from start to
finish to win the Japanese Grand Prix and take his second
straight Formula One race victory.  Two-time defending world champion Vettel followed his Sept.
23 win in Singapore by finishing 20.6 seconds ahead of Ferrariâ€™s
 Felipe Massa  at Suzuka Circuit. Kamui Kobayashi of Sauber was
third in his home race.  Championship leader  Fernando Alonso  of Ferarri spun out on
the first corner after getting a rear wheel puncture during
contact with Kimi Raikkonen. With five races remaining, Alonso
heads the standings with 194 points, four more than Vettel.  The 16th of 20 races, the Korean Grand Prix, is scheduled
